"A Century of Caruso" by Opera News Magazine 1973
(Item #: N1839-M10-B)
Special magazine issued by Opera News, the magazine from the Metropolitan Opera in NY, celebrating the 100th anniversary of Enrico Caruso's birth in 1973. Many articles and photos, 39 pages, great collectible item, size is 8.25 x 11 inches.
PRICE: $55.00 USD









"Caricatures by Enrico Caruso" - Original Book 1922 Signed by Author Marziale Sisca
(Item #: M1775-KC)
Original book from 1922, publised by La Follia di New York by Marziale Sisca, who was a friend of Enrico Caruso. Sisca asked him permission to publish this beautiful compendium of his caricatures, with hundreds of them depicting famous conductors, singers, musicians, and many of Caruso himself!.
This is the 1922 edition that came just after Caruso's death, and is signed by it's author, Marziale Sisca, inscribed to the notable Italian baritone Ferruccio Corradetti (1869-1939).
Large size (10.75 x 15.5 inches), approx. 180 unnumbered pages, complete with both covers. In original condition, very good condition
SOLD OUT








